students find more Our unique online platform connects law students with legal employers throughout the country through , internships to provide more opportunities to find the right legal job for Get Started Contact Us Expand your network through the LSC Community Broaden your network of peers, professors, and practicing attorneys swap textbooks and outlines publish your own significant papers and writing samples to showcase your value to potential legal Show your employers value Demonstrate your skill, earn money, and receive feedback for completing actual legal research and projects posted by practicing attorneys, professors, judges, and other legal Improve your skills Assess and refine your own practical legal skills through our unique partnership with And supplement your legal education with our practical skills and practice readiness course Find more jobs opportunities You are unique, and we help to match you with legal employers and companies looking for your unique combination of skills and THE UNRECOGNIZED VALUE OF A LAW STUDENT You invested time and You put life, relationships, and opportunities on All for the chance of becoming more: More educated, more skilled, and more But you did not know your value as a law student‚Äîas a future lawyer‚Äîwould be determined by only a few final exams during your first year of law All the preparation, the studying, the thousands of pages you read, the scores of outlines you wrote, the sacrifices you made, the work you put in, and the added two years it is all meaningless if you falter on your You would miss the opportunity for interviews, and the dream job you were Or perhaps that BigLaw job was never for you to begin You know what you want, and you understand that it is completely up to you to chase You are on your And neither career services nor interviews can help But even if they could, you are not interested in fighting the distribution curve of your classmates because your peers are not competitors, they are All you need is a way to showcase the underestimated value that you know you can THE LAW STUDENT PLACEMENT MODEL IS FLAWED The flawed assumptions of the current class rank and interview model misplaces the value of a law Exams = Real Life A law student final exam‚Äîwith its extraordinary fact patterns and acute focus on nuanced areas of law‚Äîaccurately simulates real life practice Exams Accurately Measure Quality A law student‚Äôs performance on these extraordinary and nuanced exams accurately predicts how successful they will be in actual practice Exams Sufficiently Measure Candidate Fit A law student‚Äôs exam scores, taken in isolation, provide enough data to connect the most qualified students with the most legal Those who have survived the law school experience can attest that the first two assumptions are almost laughable . Yet, when taken in context with the third assumption, these must indeed be the assumptions that‚Äîwhether intentional or not‚Äîform the basis of how law students are selected for And it is not laughable because limiting your future opportunities is not a joke . But interviews or flooding firms with resumes and cover letters are no longer the only Law Student Connect offers a better way to find your dream job . the Conference TRACKS SESSIONS Market Analysis learn more About the Conference The International Conference on Traditional & Alternative Medicine during Dec , Dubai, Traditional Medicine aims to gather leading educational scientists, researchers and research students to exchange & share their experiences and research results about all aspects of Traditional and Alternative Traditional Alternative Medicine main slogan is to address the challenges in making a safer , sustainable and affordable system for medication, and health through consolidating the underpinning Traditional Medicine research Traditional & Alternative Medicine conference prepares a ground for seeding new concepts and nurturing knowledge through discussions and analysis on Traditional and Alternative Medicine Traditional Medicine is planned to be an ideal rostrum for prominent practitioners from Herbal, Unani, Ayurveda and Various practices of Alternative Medicine to showcase the benefits and importance of Naturopathy . Scheduled with a vision of promoting the Natural practice implemented as a therapy is going to play it s own role in the development of applicability of Traditional Medicine as there ll be a integration of outstanding & ingenious scientists with enthusiastic graduates from all the related around the theme : " Promoting and Navigating the Future of Traditional Medicine". TRACKS SESSIONS Track : Natural Products & Herbal Medicine Natural Product Development mainly focuses on the need for less expensive alternative therapies , especially in the treatment of chronic It also involves the use of natural products in a or development The World Health Organization has been promoting traditional medicine as a source of less expensive, comprehensive medical care, especially in developing The main goal is to fully exploit the biosynthetic and therapeutic potential of untapped biodiversity for drug Many drugs listed in the modern pharmacopoeia have their origins in nature Herbal medicine differs from conventional medicine in its use of whole plants, generally as an unpurified extract herb combining (polypharmacy) and diagnostic principles based on treating "underlying causes" Track :Traditional Chinese Medicine Traditional Chinese medicine is a system of medicine partly based on the idea that an energy, called qi (say "chee"), flows along pathways in the body called In this belief, if the flow of qi along these meridians is blocked or unbalanced, illness can In China, doctors have practiced traditional Chinese medicine for thousands of years, and it is gaining in popularity in many Western Track : Acupuncture & Acupressure Acupressure is similar in practice to acupuncture (see below), only no needles are Practitioners use their hands, elbows, or feet to apply pressure to specific points along the body s "meridians" According to the theory behind acupressure, meridians are channels that carry life energy throughout the The reasoning holds that illness can occur when one of these meridians is blocked or out of balance acupressure is thought to relieve blockages so energy can flow freely again, restoring More research is needed, but pilot studies have found positive results: Acupressure might decrease nausea for chemotherapy patients and reduce anxiety in people scheduled to have surgery Acupuncture may immediately bring needles to mind, the term actually describes an array of procedures that stimulate specific points on the The variety consists of penetrating the skin with thin needles controlled by a practitioner or electrical stimulation, and it s currently used by millions of Americans each Despite its popularity, controversy over acupuncture s efficacy Some studies find it helpful for chronic pain and depression, but evidence on all counts is mixedTrusted SourceTrusted Source Track : Alterna

Stephen was a Stage 4 adenocarcinoma of the esophagus patient who was able to use his full genome sequence data to make optimal treatment decisions regarding his He obtained access to personalized immunotherapy options ‚Äì including a personalized neoantigen vaccine, which led to his surviving and thriving for three full years beyond expectations . 4 Reasons to File Your Taxes Early This Year - Dunedin Tax and Accounting COUNTY ROAD 1, DUNEDIN FL, ‚Äì | SAT BY Toggle navigation ABOUT US OUR SERVICES BLOG CONTACT US 4 Reasons to File Your Taxes Early This Year If you‚Äôre used to filing taxes, you‚Äôre probably aware that they‚Äôre due sometime around Typically, tax returns must be submitted by April , but this year, you get a couple of days‚Äô worth of That‚Äôs because April falls on a Sunday, but since the following Monday is Emancipation Day ‚Äî a Washington, , holiday ‚Äî filers get until April to get their returns over to the That said, you can submit your tax return as early as this year, and it pays to aim for that deadline, or one shortly thereafter, even if it means putting in some extra effort in the coming Here‚Äôs You‚Äôll get your money sooner An estimated % of tax filers get a refund each year, and not a small one, In fact, last year, the typical refund was $2,763 ‚Äî not exactly pocket If you have outstanding bills to pay, a vacation you‚Äôre looking to fund, or just a general desire to get your hands on the cash that‚Äôs rightfully yours, then filing early is the best way to do just Keep in mind, however, that if you‚Äôre planning to claim the Earned Income Tax Credit or the Additional Child Tax Credit, the earliest you can expect your tax refund is late Why? Because of high levels of fraud associated with these credits in particular, the IRS is required to withhold associated refunds Furthermore, this restriction applies to your entire refund, even the portion of it having nothing to do with these But if you‚Äôre not planning to claim the Earned Income Tax Credit or the Additional Child Tax, and you file your return electronically without errors, you can typically expect to get your money back within three weeks‚Äô More: Here‚Äôs the first day you can file your taxes this year More: What do I need to know if I sold stocks in ? You‚Äôll give yourself more time to address an underpayment Though most tax filers wind up with a refund each year, you may land in that rare but notable category of workers who end up owing money on their And if that‚Äôs the case, you may be in trouble, especially if your underpayment is sizable and your savings are On the other hand, if you give yourself two and a half months to come up with a plan for paying your tax debt, as opposed to waiting until the last minute, you stand a better chance of avoiding the penalties that come with paying the IRS Consider this: An estimated % of Americans have absolutely no money in the bank . If you‚Äôre one of them and realize in early April that you owe the IRS $1,000 by virtue of having underpaid your taxes, you‚Äôll have limited resources at your disposal for coming up with that lump But if you prepare your return in late January and make that discovery sooner, you‚Äôll have the opportunity to, say, take on a second job temporarily to drum up that You can avoid tax fraud Tax fraud is a major problem for filers of all ages, but believe it or not, filing your return early might actually help you avoid falling What will typically happen is that a criminal will access your information, file a return in your name, and attempt to snatch your refund in the But if you file your return early enough, that‚Äôll be a harder feat for someone to pull See, the IRS has software that‚Äôs designed to flag duplicate returns, and so if it has one on file for you and someone else then submits a second one, it‚Äôs the fraudulent return that‚Äôll get On the other hand, if a criminal beats you to the punch, it‚Äôll be on you to get things sorted out, which could not only delay your refund but also constitute a major You want to lower your stress level Let‚Äôs face it: The process can be stressful to say the least, especially if your return is complicated and requires a lot of legwork (such as needing to calculate deductions or follow up on missing documentation). One final benefit of getting your return in early is having one less thing to worry about between now and Once that return is out of your hands, you‚Äôll be able to move forward and focus your efforts and mental energy Though there are plenty of good reasons to file your taxes early this year, here‚Äôs one good reason not to: You‚Äôre missing key information that could compromise the accuracy of your While it‚Äôs helpful to get your taxes in ahead of schedule, if you don‚Äôt have the data needed to be precise, you‚Äôre better off Otherwise, you‚Äôll increase your chances of getting audited, and that‚Äôs a whole other potential nightmare to contend The Motley Fool has a disclosure policy .
